This blog post is one part of the series &ldquo;learning diary&rdquo; for a course at my university.
Goals: Besides the headline &ldquo;Didaktical-methodological Design&rdquo; an additional hint to a book was provided &ldquo;Schulmeister, Ralf, Hypermedia Learning Systems&rdquo;. Because of that I investigated a little bit about hyper media learning systems. For example what hyper media learning system means&hellip;
Turns out, hyper media is a word creation from hypertext and media. It describes systems where media content is linked to to other media content (in contrast to hypertext, where foot notes, citations and text is linked together).

Problem: Setting up a wireless adapter on Ubuntu server 12.04 LTS via CLI isn&rsquo;t THAT easy. Plug&rsquo;n&rsquo;Play doesn&rsquo;t simply work. Good thing there is Google. And a lot of helpful sites.
Target: Insert the stick (or boot with it) and connect automaticly to the preferred network
This is not a tutorial. And it&rsquo;s realy not for the uninitiated. It&rsquo;s more like a short reminder for me, or people who have a basic idea what&rsquo;s happening here&hellip;
